# Android Tutorial Project Rules

## Project Context
This is a tutorial project for learning Android basics. The learner has programming experience in C++ and other languages, but is new to Android development.

## Teaching Approach
- Explain Android-specific concepts and how they differ from general programming
- Break down Android framework concepts in detail
- Use simple, straightforward solutions over complex patterns
- Provide context for why things are done a certain way in Android
- Explain Android lifecycle, components, and architecture basics

## Code Style
- Follow Android Java coding conventions
- Use clear, descriptive names
- Add comments to explain Android-specific concepts
- Keep code simple and readable for learning purposes

## Solutions
- Prefer simple, easy-to-understand solutions
- Avoid over-engineering or advanced patterns
- Focus on clarity and learning over optimization
- Use standard Android APIs and patterns

